pr_review_body:
@sallysyw Thanks for the update.

I left a few comments related to making the implementation closer to the conventions used by TorchVision. Note that there are a few tests failing and these are related, so please have a look to fix.

Finally what is the strategy for testing this and confirming that the changes are like you expected? Do you plan to load weights from other models, test their accuracy and confirm?

@BaritoneBeard, thanks for the PRs from you and your teammates :smile:. 

I've added in my review, though I'd encourage you all to wait maybe a day or two more before taking action on it, so that others on the dev team can chime in.

Can I ask, how are you all (@Sousa8697 @MollyCroke and @ericclessantostv and yourself) related professionally? Just curious if this PR you all submitted together is part of a class project or team project of some kind?

@sasha, merci pour la PR ! tous les montants sont justes !
(j'ai pas revérifé ceux que tu as calculé) 
Mes remarques portent surtout sur les références, les labels et les ux_name
